## React Standards

- Use functional components with hooks; no class components in new code
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks (`use` prefix)
- Keep components focused: one responsibility, one reason to change
- Lift state only as high as necessary; co-locate state with the component that owns it
- Use `React.memo` only when profiling confirms a performance problem
- Prefer controlled components for forms
- Test with React Testing Library; assert on user-visible behavior, not implementation details
